[[OpenDocument]] files of type text carry .odt extension.

Emacs has varied support for working with .odt files.

==Create==
[[OrgMode]] files can now be exported to OpenDocumentText. 

See [http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-orgmode/2011-01/msg01210.html announcement in Orgmode mailing list] and [http://orgmode.org/worg/org-faq.html#convert-to-open-office Orgmode FAQ entry].

==View and edit==

From 2006 there is a preliminary support for that.
See odf-mode.el: http://www.cb1.com/~john/computing/emacs/lisp/editing/odf-mode.el.

YMMV :-)

==Convert==

Use [https://bitbucket.org/josemaria.alkala/odt2org/wiki/Home odt2org] to convert.odt files to OrgMode. The tool is Python-based and can handles lists, links, images, tables etc. 

Once a document is exporter to .org file, converting it to other file formats like HTML, PDF, LaTeX, DocBook, MediaWiki is quite a breeze.
